      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "# How to play storm \n__Solos__\nThe main things you want to get are the gloves and the Skyline Deployer. The rest of your inventory should consist of heals and possibly a shotgun depending on if there is surge or not. Please make sure you follow #\uD83C\uDF29・surge-tips if you are in a high player count lobby.  When the 5th zone appears. You can get a patch up and more med kits from a vending machine. Use the vending machines to your advantage as they are a core part to early mid game strategy. Plan your rotates out carefully. Make sure you use things like the Flowberry Mist (or someone else’s) or other people’s builds to rotate. Eventually when you are safe you can take height without being lobby focused. Start your skybase somewhere safe and get as high as possible. Your main goal should be to take a very high height. Pre-edit your walls and start moving to circle. In the event that you get show down or run out of mats, use the gloves to launch you in the air 4 times and then use the skyline deployer. This will make you very hard to spot. Keep on using the skyline deployer to rotate to circle until it comes down to a heal off. Because you have an inventory filled with heals. You should win heal off by a significant margin.",
