    {
      "id": "1494003151169257665",
      "type": "Default",
      "timestamp": "2026-04-15T17:55:08.475+02:00",
      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "__Duos__\nThe strategy I said for solos can be used, but it is more difficult because your duo is a liability. The best bet is to play storm until mid-game. where you use vending machines to outlive the 2 tick storm. Once you out-heal storm and rotate to the 5 tick zone, you need to survive as long as possible for endgame. Try to save your meds and rotation for as long as possible and rotate with other people's builds. Try to take and hold height as it will be a win-con in your strategy. In the event that you run out of mats, use the skyline deployer with your duo. Alternatively, you can have the fragger survive on the bottom while the IGL takes height but it is not recommended as there will be people who fight for height. Make sure to have a method to go around fall damage as people like to shoot you down. If your rotate is not 100% safe, you can go around in storm by using your medkits to out-heal it (only use this for late end game). Try not to fight unless forced. In the last zone or when the zone closes, have somebody drop their meds (preferably the fragger), and die. The person playing heal off will then out heal last place. If you know that you can kill the last guy (very risky), have the fragger as the healer, and kill the last guy. This is a high-risk, high-reward play.",
